<h2>National Poll Average</h2>



<iframe scrolling="no" src="//plot.ly/~amksarti/140.embed?showlink=false&amp;modebar=false" width="800vw" height="500vh" frameborder="0"></iframe>



<p>This poll average is the result of a smoothing cubic spline fitted to our dataset of all national polls collected in Germany. You can access the complete database of polls at <a href="https://europeelects.eu/data/">https://europeelects.eu/data/</a></p>



<h2>Government</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-table is-style-stripes"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Head of State</strong> <strong>(President)</strong></td><td>Frank-Walter Steinmeier (SPD-S&amp;D)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Head of Government</strong> <strong>(Chancellor)</strong></td><td>Angela Merkel (CDU-EPP)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Parties in Government</strong></td><td>Christian Democratic Union of Germany (CDU-EPP)<br>Social Democratic Party of Germany (SPD-S&amp;D)<br>Christian Social Union in Bavaria (CSU-EPP)</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<h2>Parties</h2>



<div class="wp-block-media-text alignwide has-pale-cyan-blue-background-color has-background" style="grid-template-columns:18% auto"><figure class="wp-block-media-text__media"><img loading="lazy" width="1024" height="304" src="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1920px-Cdu-logo.svg-1024x304.png" alt="" class="wp-image-7009509 size-full" srcset="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1920px-Cdu-logo.svg-1024x304.png 1024w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1920px-Cdu-logo.svg-300x89.png 300w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1920px-Cdu-logo.svg-768x228.png 768w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1920px-Cdu-logo.svg-1536x456.png 1536w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1920px-Cdu-logo.svg-540x160.png 540w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1920px-Cdu-logo.svg-1080x321.png 1080w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/1920px-Cdu-logo.svg.png 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure><div class="wp-block-media-text__content">
<p><strong>Christlich Demokratische Union Deutschlands</strong> (CDU)<br>Christian Democratic Union of Germany<br><strong>Leader (CDU):</strong> Annegret Kramp-Karrenbauer<br><strong>Orientation:</strong> Centre-right<br><strong>EP Affiliation:</strong> EPP (<a aria-label="undefined (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.eppgroup.eu/about-us/members#mep:s1UAL6sanR5/vTSpeTooHoDBjx072gabFEI8636uDe/p16kSc6ehjSoIuSgw5h1g94Iqbpg9EVe2tXs6I3hZQQ" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">EPP-EP</a>, <a aria-label="undefined (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.epp.eu/parties-and-partners/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">EPP Party</a>, <a href="https://www.idc-cdi.com/parties/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">CDI</a>, <a href="https://www.idu.org/members/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">IDU</a>, <a aria-label="undefined (opens in a new tab)" href="https://pace.coe.int/en/members/7889?lang=EN" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">EPP-PACE</a>)<br><strong>EU Stance:</strong> In favour of EU integration (<a href="https://europeelects.eu/european-union/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Chapel-Hill data</a>)<br><br><strong>Note:</strong> Registered in all regions (<em>Bundesländer</em>) but Bavaria; forms group in the national parliament and in PACE with CSU (EPP)</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-media-text alignwide has-background" style="background-color:#FF7A7A;grid-template-columns:18% auto"><figure class="wp-block-media-text__media"><img loading="lazy" width="360" height="360" src="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/360px-SPD_logo.svg_.png" alt="" class="wp-image-838 size-full" srcset="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/360px-SPD_logo.svg_.png 360w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/360px-SPD_logo.svg_-150x150.png 150w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/360px-SPD_logo.svg_-300x300.png 300w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/360px-SPD_logo.svg_-100x100.png 100w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px" /></figure><div class="wp-block-media-text__content">
<p><strong>Sozialdemokratische Partei Deutschlands</strong> (SPD)<br>Social Democratic Party of Germany<br><strong>Leaders:</strong>  Norbert Walter-Borjans &amp; Saskia Esken<br><strong>Orientation:</strong> Centre-left<br><strong>EP Affiliation:</strong> S&amp;D (<a aria-label="undefined (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.socialistsanddemocrats.eu/who-we-are/our-members/national-parties" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">S&amp;D</a>, <a href="https://www.pes.eu/en/members/parties-map/#list" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">PES</a>, <a aria-label="undefined (opens in a new tab)" href="https://pace.coe.int/en/members/8284?lang=EN" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"></a><a href="https://progressive-alliance.info/network/parties-and-organisations/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">PA</a>, <a aria-label="undefined (opens in a new tab)" href="https://pace.coe.int/en/members/8284?lang=EN" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">SOC</a>)<br><strong>EU Stance:</strong> Strongly in favour of EU integration (<a href="https://europeelects.eu/european-union/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Chapel-Hill data</a>) </p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-media-text alignwide has-background" style="background-color:#999a9b;grid-template-columns:18% auto"><figure class="wp-block-media-text__media"><img loading="lazy" width="1000" height="460" src="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/1000px-Alternative-fuer-Deutschland-Logo-2013.svg_.png" alt="" class="wp-image-839 size-full" srcset="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/1000px-Alternative-fuer-Deutschland-Logo-2013.svg_.png 1000w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/1000px-Alternative-fuer-Deutschland-Logo-2013.svg_-300x138.png 300w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/1000px-Alternative-fuer-Deutschland-Logo-2013.svg_-768x353.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" /></figure><div class="wp-block-media-text__content">

</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-media-text alignwide has-text-color has-background" style="background-color:#994B4B;color:#f1f1f3;grid-template-columns:18% auto"><figure class="wp-block-media-text__media"><img loading="lazy" width="400" height="240" src="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/400px-Flag_of_Die_Linke.svg_.png" alt="" class="wp-image-841 size-full" srcset="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/400px-Flag_of_Die_Linke.svg_.png 400w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/400px-Flag_of_Die_Linke.svg_-300x180.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></figure><div class="wp-block-media-text__content">

</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-media-text alignwide has-light-green-cyan-background-color has-background" style="grid-template-columns:20% auto"><figure class="wp-block-media-text__media"><img loading="lazy" width="400" height="241" src="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/400px-ÖDP-Logo.svg.png" alt="" class="wp-image-1003855 size-full" srcset="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/400px-ÖDP-Logo.svg.png 400w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/400px-ÖDP-Logo.svg-300x181.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></figure><div class="wp-block-media-text__content">
<p><strong>Ökologisch-Demokratische Partei </strong>(ÖDP)<br>Ecological Democratic Party<br><strong>Leader:</strong> Christian Rechholz<br><strong>Orientation:</strong> Green party politics, moderate social conservativism<br><strong>EP Affiliation:</strong> Greens/EFA (<a href="https://www.greens-efa.eu/en/our-group/meps/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Greens/EFA</a>, <a aria-label="undefined (opens in a new tab)" href="https://www.w-e-p.org/members/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">WEP</a>)<br><strong>EU Stance:</strong> In favour of EU integration </p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-media-text alignwide has-light-green-cyan-background-color has-background" style="grid-template-columns:20% auto"><figure class="wp-block-media-text__media"><img loading="lazy" width="400" height="150" src="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/400px-Piratenpartei_Deutschland_Logo_01.svg.png" alt="" class="wp-image-1003857 size-full" srcset="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/400px-Piratenpartei_Deutschland_Logo_01.svg.png 400w, https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/400px-Piratenpartei_Deutschland_Logo_01.svg-300x113.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></figure><div class="wp-block-media-text__content">
<p><strong>Piratenpartei Deutschland</strong> (Piraten)<br>Pirate Party Germany<br><strong>Leader:</strong> Sebastian Alscher<br><strong>Orientation:</strong> Pirate politics, social liberalism<br><strong>EP Affiliation:</strong> Greens/EFA (<a href="https://www.greens-efa.eu/en/our-group/meps/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Greens/EFA</a>, <a href="https://european-pirateparty.eu/members/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">PPEU</a>, <a aria-label="undefined (opens in a new tab)" href="https://pp-international.net/pirate-parties/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">PPI</a>)<br><strong>EU Stance:</strong> Strongly in favour of EU integration (<a href="https://europeelects.eu/european-union/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Chapel-Hill data</a>)</p>
</div></div>



<div class="wp-block-media-text alignwide has-background" style="background-color:#6fabf3;grid-template-columns:20% auto"><figure class="wp-block-media-text__media"><img loading="lazy" width="250" height="64" src="https://europeelects.eu/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/250px-FamilienPartei_Logo2007.svg.png" alt="" class="wp-image-6009016 size-full"/></figure><div class="wp-block-media-text__content">
